✅ Full Solution (Java)
javaclass Solution {
    public int maxProductPath(int[][] grid) {
        int MOD = 1_000_000_007;
        int m = grid.length, n = grid[0].length;

        long[][] maxDp = new long[m][n];
        long[][] minDp = new long[m][n];

        // Base case
        maxDp[0][0] = minDp[0][0] = grid[0][0];

        // First row — can only come from left
        for (int j = 1; j < n; j++) {
            long val = grid[0][j];
            long p1 = maxDp[0][j-1] * val;
            long p2 = minDp[0][j-1] * val;
            maxDp[0][j] = Math.max(p1, p2);
            minDp[0][j] = Math.min(p1, p2);
        }

        // First column — can only come from above
        for (int i = 1; i < m; i++) {
            long val = grid[i][0];
            long p1 = maxDp[i-1][0] * val;
            long p2 = minDp[i-1][0] * val;
            maxDp[i][0] = Math.max(p1, p2);
            minDp[i][0] = Math.min(p1, p2);
        }

        // Fill rest
        for (int i = 1; i < m; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j < n; j++) {
                long val = grid[i][j];
                long p1 = maxDp[i-1][j] * val;
                long p2 = minDp[i-1][j] * val;
                long p3 = maxDp[i][j-1] * val;
                long p4 = minDp[i][j-1] * val;
                maxDp[i][j] = Math.max(Math.max(p1, p2), Math.max(p3, p4));
                minDp[i][j] = Math.min(Math.min(p1, p2), Math.min(p3, p4));
            }
        }

        long maxProd = maxDp[m-1][n-1];
        return maxProd < 0 ? -1 : (int)(maxProd % MOD);
    }
}

⏱️ Complexity
ValueTimeO(m × n) — visit each cell onceSpaceO(m × n) — two DP tables (reducible to O(n) with rolling array)